The title is a takeoff on the title of a 1905 silent comedy short, &quot;The Whole Dam Family and the Family Dog&quot; (sequel to another 1905 short, &quot;I. B. Dam and the Dam Family&quot;), which also supplied subject matter for a raft of comic picture postcards. Use of the word &quot;damn&quot; was considered very risque in polite circles then, and even spelling it without the final &quot;n&quot; could bring a frisson of titillation to sensitive auditors. Here is an example of a &quot;Dam Family&quot; postcard:
<a href="http://www.slv.vic.gov.au/pcards/0/0/1/doc/pc001380.shtml">www.slv.vic.gov.au/pcards/0/0/1/doc/pc001380.shtml</a>

Incidentally, &quot;darnd&quot; above is a misspelling. It should be &quot;darned.&quot;
